</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thelix@thesteelwarrior>Thelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 10:29:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5007.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animation-station.com/cartoon/images/cart0037.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Weapon Experts</span><hr size=1> With you only being level 17 I wouldn't worry too much about what weapon to use out of that list because all of them will be excellent weapons at that level. As a range I would think you would want to work up first 1hs, then 2hs then 1hb (can't remember the last time I saw a ranger swinging a 2hb, not to say they don't but personally I don't remember any)<br>
<br>
I would say duel wield the Lammy in mainhand and use the Guard Captains Mallet in offhand. raise your 1hs skill each level then use the 32 36 or 35 35 2hs to raise your 2hs skill.<br>
<br>
All the range I know use 1hs in both hands and switch out to a 2hs weapon when melee'ing. If you have the resources I would keep all the skill maxed out because you never know what weapon will fall into your lap someday. If i were to rate which ones to use in order I would say:<br>
<br>
1. 1hs<br>
2. 2hs<br>
3. 1hb<br>
4. 2hb<br>
5. Piercing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nailened>Nailened</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 10:37:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5007.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Weapon Experts</span><hr size=1> The first reply is good advice.  At level 17 you could grab a cracked staff if ya had to so &quot;uber twink weapons&quot; only really count for so much at level 17.  I'd personally say since you will NOT have a good pri hand damage bonus I'd go with something kind of stout damage wise in pri and then a good off hander.  The other person is 100% correct in that you should keep all weapons skills maxed if possible or at least very high in case you get a chance to buy or loot a good weapon.  I'd go the 12 / 20 in primary and frosty off hand even though it won't proc for a good long time yet.  I would work on the 2h stuff too though.  At least one of 2hb or 2hs.   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Me - Brueno Baldnoggin<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362323"> 63 Dwarf Warrior</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
